-- Smart Wind to Say It Has Connection to U.K. National Grid, Times Reports
-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 2010-09-27T01:38:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/smart-wind-says-it-has-u-k-national-grid-connection-times-says.html
The Smart Wind Consortium, a joint
venture between a unit of Siemens AG and Mainstream Renewable
Power Ltd., will today say it has secured a connection to the
U.K.’s National Grid, boosting the prospects of its proposed 15
billion-pound ($24 billion) wind project being built off the
coast of Yorkshire, England, the London-based Times reported,
citing Andy Kinsella, the group’s chairman.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
